th%20overt%20Nazi%20symbols%20like%20the%20swastika%20in%20their%20logos%20and%20others%20with%20taglines%20like%20%26quot%3BYour%20pro-White%20policy%20destination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-feud-between-elon-musks-twitter-and-substack-explained-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESubstack%3C%2Fa%3E%20founder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-a-job-at-substack-according-to-cofounder-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHamish%20McKenzie%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2F%40hamish%2Fnote%2Fc-45811343%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresponse%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20criticism%2C%20and%20reaffirmed%20the%20decision%20not%20to%20remove%20or%20demonetize%20those%20blogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EI%20just%20want%20to%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20we%20don't%20like%20Nazis%20either%20%E2%80%94%20we%20wish%20no-one%20held%20those%20views.%20But%20some%20people%20do%20hold%20those%20and%20other%20extreme%20views.%20Given%20that%2C%20we%20don't%20think%20that%20censorship%20(including%20through%20demonetizing%20publications)%20makes%20the%20problem%20go%20away%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20worse.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20Substack%20writers%2C%20some%20of%20them%20among%20the%20most%20prominent%20and%20popular%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20also%20signed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fhome%2Fpost%2Fp-139757629%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20that%20they%20stand%20by%20Substack's%20decision.%20It%20is%20simply%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20they%20said.%20Substack%20didn't%20respond%20to%20my%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20this%20all%20seems%20to%20be%20omitting%3A%20the%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20a%20debate%20about%20free%20expression%2C%20this