5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22941%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22161331%2Fimage-1663.png%20821w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22161331%2Fimage-1663-300x202.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690381%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22634%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWomen%20engaging%20in%20sports%20for%20peacebuilding%20at%20Basugaon%20village%2C%20Chirang%20district%2C%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20are%20often%20caught%20in%20the%20web%20of%20statelessness%2C%20more%20so%20than%20men%2C%20because%20authorities%20often%20reject%20the%20documents%20they%20need%20to%20prove%20Indian%20citizenship.%20This%20issue%20essentially%20arises%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20poor%20women%20have%20fewer%20documents%20to%20establish%20their%20long-term%20ancestral%20residence%20in%20Assam.%20Consequently%2C%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20non-citizens%20are%20women%2C%20and%20they%20are%20subsequently%20detained%20in%20detention%20centres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20women%20in%20the%20detention%20centres%20are%20middle-aged%20and%20mothers.%20Given%20that%20motherhood%20is%20given%20prime%20importance%20in%20most%20societies%2C%20many%20women%20take%20their%20children%20to%20detention%20centres%20with%20them%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20care%20of%20them%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20gender-insensitive%20environment%20at%20detention%20centres%20do%20not%20take%20into%20account%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20mothers%20and%20their%20children%20who%20might%20accompany%20them%2C%20thus%20making%20the%20experience%20of%20female%20detainees%20more%20difficult%20to%20navigate.%20The%20case%20of%20Fatima%20Begum*%20can%20best%20substantiate%20this%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFatima%20Begum%2C%20from%20Cachar%20district%2C%20experienced%2010%20years%20of%20detention%20in%20three%20different%20centres%20with%20her%20daughter.%20She%20was%20sent%20a%20notice%20from%20the%20Foreigners%E2%80%99%20Tribunal%20when%20she%20was%20two%20months%20pregnant.%20About%20eight%20months%20later%2C%20she%20was%20declared%20a%20foreigner%20as%20a%20result%20of%20not%20being%20able%20to%20produce%20the%20necessary%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22163049%2Fimage-1664.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22975%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22163049%2Fimage-1664.png%20822w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22163049%2Fimage-1664-300x209.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690387%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20woman%20grabs%20the%20Frisbee%20disc%20during%20the%20parents%E2%80%99%20session%20at%20Basugaon%20village%2C%20Chirang%20district%2C%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20she%20had%20given%20birth%20to%20a%20daughter%2C%20who%20was%20less%20than%20two%20months%20old.%20Reflecting%20back%20on%20the%20day%20she%20was%20taken%20to%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20police%20officers%20came%20to%20take%20me%2C%20I%20told%20them%20clearly%20that%20I%20would%20not%20go%20without%20my%20daughter.%20She%20was%20only%2045%20days%20old%20at%20that%20time%2C%20how%20could%20I%20go%20without%20her%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20recalling%20her%20time%20at%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20along%20with%20her%20infant%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20cut%20my%20saree%20into%20pieces%20to%20cover%20my%20child.%E2%80%9D%20She%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20I%20would%20feel%20uncomfortable%20while%20breastfeeding%20in%20the%20presence%20of%2010%20other%20people.%20But%20slowly%20I%20got%20accustomed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBodies%20of%20the%20female%20detainees%20chosen%20as%20sites%20of%20abuse%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20partition%20of%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20into%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20is%20merely%20an%20example%20reflecting%20the%20way%20in%20which%20the%20gender%20question%20manifests%20itself%20during%20sensitive%20border%20relations%2C%20conflicts%20or%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%20of%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%2C%20where%20women%20have%20reportedly%20been%20subject%20to%20physical%20violence%20of%20several%20forms%2C%20reflects%20how%20violence%20on%20the%20bodies%20of%20women%20during%20sensitive%20border%20relations%20continues%20to%20manifest%20even%20today.%20Given%20that%20all%20detainees%20are%20inherently%20perceived%20as%20foreigners%2C%20the%20authorities%20often%20perpetrate%20violence%20on%20the%20detainees%20to%20demarcate%20the%20boundaries%20between%20%E2%80%98us%20Indians%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Bangladeshi%20other%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaheen%20Nessa*%2C%20who%20also%20lived%20in%20detention%20for%2010%20years%2C%20was%20three%20months%20pregnant%20when%20she%20was%20detained.%20She%20claimed%20that%20she%20could%20feel%20the%20movements%20of%20her%20baby%20before%20moving%20to%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20and%20hence%20realised%20that%20the%20baby%20was%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20she%20turned%20six%20months%20pregnant%2C%20one%20day%2C%20the%20authorities%20forcefully%20pushed%20a%20tetanus%20injection%2C%20which%20she%20claims%20was%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20death%20of%20her%20child.%20She%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20though%20I%20told%20them%20I%20do%20not%20want%20the%20injection%20to%20be%20pushed%2C%20they%20did%20not%20listen%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20gave%20birth%20to%20a%20dead%20boy.%20They%20have%20killed%20my%20child.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENessa%20also%20recalled%20how%20her%20co-inmates%20were%20subject%20to%20physical%20violence.%20She%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20witnessed%20other%20people%20being%20tortured%20as%20well.%20One%20day%2C%20a%20woman%20did%20not%20know%20that%20rice%20was%20being%20served.%20She%20went%20late%20and%20was%20denied%20food.%20When%20she%20asked%20for%20food%2C%20she%20was%20beaten%20up.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bodies%20of%20women%20become%20receptacles%20of%20violence%20at%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20detention%20centres.%20In%20a%20space%20that%20is%20unequipped%20to%20facilitate%20even%20the%20basic%20requirements%20of%20humans%2C%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20needs%20and%20requirements%20of%20women%2C%20mothers%20and%20children%20only%20remains%20a%20distant%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Names%20of%20interviewees%20have%20been%20changed%20to%20maintain%20confidentiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20part%20of%20an%20explainer%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%E2%80%99%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20team.%20Read%20the%20first%20part%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdetainees-sharing-cells-with-criminals-human-rights-violations-in-assams-detention-centres%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThese%20explainers%20explore%20the%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%20as%20spaces%20violating%20human%20rights%20and%20disproportionately%20affecting%20migrants.%20These%20are%20penned%20down%20from%20the%20documented%20findings%20of%20a%20recent%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20edition.%20Click%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazaadawaazcnes.wordpress.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20access%20the%20work%20of%20Azaad%20Awaaz%2C%20an%20initiative%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20working%20on%20issues%20of%20social%20exclusion%2C%20marginalisation%2C%20and%20discrimination%20experienced%20by%20vulnerable%2C%20precarious%20communities%20across%20India.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAll%20photographs%20have%20been%20taken%20by%20CNES%20researchers%20during%20field%20work%20in%20Assam.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20Samragnee%20Chakraborty%20and%20Hima%20Trisha%20M.%20are%20Senior%20Research%20Analysts%20(CNES).%20Yashovardhan%20Chaturvedi%2C%20Nitya%20Arora%2C%20Rieshav%20Chakraborty%20and%20Aman%20Chain%20are%20Research%20Assistants%20with%20CNES.%20The%20authors%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Dr.%20Salah%20Punathil%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad%20for%20his%20guidance%20and%20support.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703250011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F10074737%2FIMG_3446.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fid-cut-my-saree-into-pieces-to-cover-my-child-how-women-survive-in-assams-detention-centres%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Most%20women%20in%20the%20detention%20centres%20are%20middle-aged%20and%20mothers.%20However%2C%20the%20gender-insensitive%20environment%20at%20detention%20centres%20do%20not%20take%20into%20account%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20mothers%20and%20their%20children%20who%20might%20accompany%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fid-cut-my-saree-into-pieces-to-cover-my-child-how-women-survive-in-assams-detention-centres%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dunki'%20gets%20a%20standing%20ovation%20in%20NY%20theatre%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703249424000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsta