e%2C%20the%20Israeli%20Defence%20Forces%20(IDF)%20have%20done%20little%20to%20achieve%20their%20stated%20aims%20%E2%80%93%20the%20rescue%20of%20those%20captured%20by%20Hamas%20and%20the%20elimination%20of%20Hamas%20%E2%80%93%20by%20military%20means.%20Of%20the%20people%20%E2%80%93%20civilians%20and%20military%20%E2%80%93%20that%20Hamas%20had%20captured%2C%20the%20IDF%20has%20rescued%20one%2C%20and%20murdered%20three.%20Hamas%20claims%20others%20have%20died%20due%20to%20Israeli%20bombing%20and%20shelling%2C%20but%20this%20is%20impossible%20to%20verify.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20eliminating%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Israelis%20claim%20that%20the%20kill%20ratio%20is%20two%20civilians%20to%20one%20military%20target%2C%20and%20that%20this%20is%20a%20good%20ratio.%20If%20this%20is%20true%2C%20then%20about%206%2C500%20of%20the%2020%2C000%20killed%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20would%20have%20been%20military%20targets.%20If%20the%20upper%20limit%20of%20estimated%20Hamas%20personnel%20is%20taken%20to%20be%2030%2C000%2C%20then%20it%20also%20means%20that%20the%20IDF%20is%20prepared%20to%20kill%20approximately%20another%2070%2C000%20people%2C%20of%20whom%20the%20vast%20majority%20will%20be%20civilians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20given%20that%20the%20IDF%20killed%20three%20of%20the%20people%20it%20was%20claiming%20to%20be%20rescuing%2C%20after%20they%20had%20stripped%20their%20shirt%2C%20scrawled%20SOS%20in%20Hebrew%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-hamas-war-killed-hostages-were-holding-white-flag%2Flive-67742012%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewere%20waving%20a%20white%20flag%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20IDF%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20distinguish%20between%20combatants%20and%20non-combatants%20is%20in%20doubt.%20Moreover%2C%20with%20about%20three%20IDF%20personnel%20being%20killed%20daily%20during%20military%20operations%20seems%20to%20indicate%20that%20neither%20the%20will%20to%20fight%2C%20nor%20the%20ability%2C%20of%20Hamas%20has%20been%20severely%20degraded.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20stated%20goals%20%E2%80%93%20the%20liberation%20of%20those%20captured%2C%20most%20of%20them%20civilians%20and%20many%20of%20them%20elderly%20or%20children%2C%20and%20the%20elimination%20of%20a%20militant%20group%20that%20wilfully%20murdered%20hundreds%20of%20civilians%20%E2%80%93%20were%20legitimate.%20But%20the%20way%20that%20Israel%20has%20prosecuted%20this%20war%20indicates%20either%20the%20IDF%20is%20entirely%20incompetent%2C%20or%20other%20unstated%20goals%20are%20taking%20precedence.%20Since%20October%207%2C%20the%20world%20has%20seen%20Israel%20killing%20thousands%20of%20civilians%20and%20taking%20hundreds%20more%20civilian%20captives.%20Israel%20may%20justify%20these%20actions%20as%20%E2%80%98retaliatory%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20the%20end%20result%20is%20a%20(much%20larger)%20replica%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20atrocities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20release%20of%20110%20civilians%20by%20Hamas%20in%20the%20first%20round%20of%20ceasefire%20negotiations%2C%20initially%20resisted%20by%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20war%20cabinet%2C%20showed%20that%20there%20were%20other%20ways%20to%20do%20things.%20Since%20Israel%20released%20240%20Palestinian%20women%20and%20children%20as%20part%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20though%2C%20it%20showed%20the%20world%20that%20Hamas%20was%20hardly%20the%20only%20actor%20kidnapping%20and%20detaining%20civilians.%20Israel%20tries%20Palestinians%20under%20a%20military%20court%2C%20which%20has%20a%20conviction%20rate%20of%2096-99%25%20for%20any%20act%20of%20resisting%20its%20military%20occupation.%20It%20also%20holds%20hundreds%20as%20detainees%20even%20without%20conviction%2C%20often%20for%20years.%20The%20release%20of%20Palestinian%20women%20and%20children%20led%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F12%2F21%2F1217758546%2Fhamas-support-palestinians-west-bank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esurge%20of%20support%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20Hamas%20in%20both%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20and%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scale%20and%20manner%20of%20Israeli%20military%20operations%20are%20such%20that%20even%20its%20committed%20allies%20%E2%80%93%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20most%20European%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20are%20starting%20to%20use%20words%20like%20%E2%80%9Cindiscriminate%20bombing%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Ckilling%20rage%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20slowly%20starting%20to%20assert%20that%20the%20killing%20has%20to%20stop%2C%20or%20at%20least%2C%20be%20contained.%20Even%20Germany%2C%20which%20has%20defined%20the%20defence%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Staatsr%C3%A4son%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20or%20national%20interest%20%E2%80%93%20due%20to%20the%20crimes%20of%20the%20Nazis%2C%20has%20now%20started%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcease-fire-in-gaza-why-germany-abstained-in-un-votes%2Fa-67772509%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eabstain%20from%20UN%20votes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20rather%20than%20merely%20following%20Israeli%20points.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENone%20of%20this%20has%20impacted%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20strategies.%20Partially%2C%20this%20is%20because%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lowyinstitute.org%2Fpublications%2Fisrael-war-about-more-recovering-hostages-destroying-hamas-it-could-last-long-time%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etwo%20of%20the%20unstated%20goals%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20IDF%20campaign%20are%20to%20restore%20the%20deterrence%20capability%20of%20Israel%2C%20and%20to%20re-establish%20trust%20between%20the%20state%20and%20society%20that%20such%20a%20massive%20security%20failure%20will%20not%20happen%20again.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20military%20campaign%20is%20as%20much%20a%20psychological%20operation%20%E2%80%93%20directed%20both%20at%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20enemies%20and%20its%20own%20population%20to%20recreate%20an%20aura%20of%20invincibility%20that%20the%20Hamas%20October%207%20attacks%20tore%20apart.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20meshes%20well%20with%20the%20political%20aims%20of%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20and%20his%20extreme%20right%20cabinet.%20Netanyahu%20has%20always%20been%20a%20believer%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9CIron%20Wall%E2%80%9D%20concept%20enunciated%20by%20the%20Russian-born%20Ze%E2%80%99ev%20Jabotinsky.%20In%20his%20famous%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fen.jabotinsky.org%2Fmedia%2F9747%2Fthe-iron-wall.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E1923%20essay%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20same%20name%2C%20Jabotinsky%20stated%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20would%20not%20abandon%20resisting%20the%20colonisation%20of%20their%20land%20by%20Zionists%20until%20all%20hope%20of%20resistance%20was%20defeated%20by%20an%20iron%20wall%20of%20force.%20The%20survival%20of%20any%20form%20of%20resistance%20among%20the%20Palestinians%20is%20anathema%20for%20Netanyahu%2C%20and%20the%20catastrophic%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20proved%20that%20he%20was%20deluded%20in%20believing%20he%20had%20bludgeoned%20Palestinians%20into%20total%20submission.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20IDF%20campaign%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20pursue%20this%20goal%20%E2%80%93%20to%20annihilate%20completely%20any%20Palestinian%20resistance%20to%20the%20supremacism%20that%20Netanyahu%20and%20his%20ilk%20espouse.%20It%20is%20a%20goal%20that%20is%20next%20to%20impossible%20to%20achieve.%20As%20the%20history%20of%20slave%20revolts%20across%20the%20millennia%20show%2C%20going%20back%20even%20to%20the%20Biblical%20story%20of%20Moses%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20much%20you%20repress%20a%20people%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20resistance%20and%20the%20desire%20for%20freedom%20do%20not%20die.%20Nonetheless%2C%20Netanyahu%20will%20continue%20to%20try%2C%20and%20murder%20tens%20of%20thousands%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703244618000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22144413%2FF-0iKk5W0AE8x3I.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnetanyahus-supremacist-war%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20an%20overwhelming%20military%20advantage%2C%20Israel%20is%20far%20from%20meeting%20its%20own%20stated%20goals%20of%20the%20war%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%20This%20may%20be%20because%20Netanyahu%20is%20pursuing%20a%20different%20endgame.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnetanyahus-supremacist-war%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lupin%20expands%20global%20portfolio%20with%20acquisition%20of%20assets%20from%20Sanofi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703244505000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2018-09%2F26%2Ffull%2F1537979166-0877.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flupin-expands-global-portfolio-with-acquisition-of-assets-from-sanofi-123122200693_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20deal%20involves%20the%20acquisition%20of%20a%20portfolio%20of%20accretive%20established%20products%20in%20Europe%20and%20Canada%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flupin-expands-global-portfolio-with-acquisition-of-assets-from-sanofi-123122200693_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flupin-expands-global-portfolio-with-acquisition-of-assets-from-sanofi-123122200693_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flupin-expands-global-portfolio-with-acquisition-of-assets-from-sanofi-123122200693_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20takes%20aim%20at%20financial%20institutions%20with%20new%20Russia%20sanctions%20authority%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703243314000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106212806%2Cimgsize-1205144.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-takes-aim-at-financial-institutions-with-new-russia-sanctions-authority%2Farticleshow%2F106212661.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106212661.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUS%20president%20Biden%20to%20sign%20executive%20order%20allowing%20sanctions%20on%20financial%20institutions%20aiding%20Russia's%20evasion%3B%20order%20also%20bans%20products%20from%20Russia%20processed%20in%20third%20countries%2C%20including%20seafood%20and%20diamonds%3B%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Yellen%20states%20that%20the%20new%20tools%20will%20be%20used%20against%20Russia's%20war%20machine%3B%20senior%20officials%20warn%20financial%20institutions%20to%20stop%20supplying%20Russian%20defense%20sector%20or%20face%20sanctions%3B%20US%2C%20EU%2C%20and%20UK%20have%20imposed%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20since%20the%20Ukraine%20invasion%3B%20new%20order%20targets%20networks%20and%20front%20companies%20that%20aid%20in%20sanctions%20evasion%3B%20provisions%20take%20effect%20immediately%20after%20signing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-takes-aim-at-financial-institutions-with-new-russia-sanctions-authority%2Farticleshow%2F106212661.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-takes-aim-at-financial-institutions-with-new-russia-sanctions-authority%2Famp_articleshow%2F106212661.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-takes-aim-at-financial-institutions-with-new-russia-sanctions-authority%2Famp_articleshow%2F106212661.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Assam's%20Amendment%20to%20Police%20Act%20Has%20Put%20Constraints%20on%20Holding%20Misconduct%20Accountable%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22153213%2FF9vo5rrWsAAbeUY.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Himanta%20Biswa%20Sarma%20government%E2%80%99s%20amendment%20to%20the%20Assam%20Police%20Act%20in%202022%20has%20%E2%80%9Cseverely%20constrained%E2%80%9D%20enforcing%20accountability%20of%20the%20police%20personnel%20guilty%20of%20serious%20misconduct%2C%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20based%20study%20has%20revealed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%2C%20%E2%80%9CPolice%20Complaints%20Authority%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20Status%2C%20Gaps%2C%20Challenges%E2%80%9D%2C%20published%20by%20the%20well-known%20rights%20international%20rights%20body%2C%20the%20Commonwealth%20Human%20Rights%20Initiative%20(CHRI)%2C%20has%20underlined%20that%20though%20Assam%20is%20among%20a%20few%20states%20to%20have%20a%20functional%20State%20Police%20Accountability%20Commission%20(SPAC)%20since%202008%20as%20per%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20directive%2C%20the%20amendment%20made%20to%20the%20state%20Police%20Act%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20government%20in%202022%20has%20severely%20compromised%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20independence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20September%202022%2C%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20demand%20to%20send%20the%20Bill%20to%20a%20select%20committee%20was%20rejected%20by%20the%20speaker%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20walk-out%20by%20the%20opposition%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flegal.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findustry%2Fbill-to-amend-assam-police-act-passed-congress-gogoi-stage-walk-out%2F94314989%5C%22%3Epassing%20of%20the%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20voice%20vote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CHRI%20study%2C%20based%20on%20data%20supplied%20by%20the%20Commission%2C%20has%20shown%20that%20the%20amendment%20had%20weakened%20the%20accountability%20of%20police%20personnel%20by%20%E2%80%9Creducing%20the%20mandate%20of%20SPAC%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%20has%20pointed%20out%20that%20before%20the%20amendment%2C%20the%20commission%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20empowered%20with%20advisory%20and%20guidance%20providing%20functions%20with%20respect%20to%20misconduct%20as%20well%20and%20it%20served%20as%20an%20important%20check%20against%20biased%20inquiries%20and%20provided%20a%20powerful%20fillip%20to%20police%20accountability.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20with%20the%20state%20legislature%20amending%20the%20Police%20Act%20which%20included%20restructuring%20the%20district-level%20authorities%2C%20it%20has%20become%20difficult%20to%20demand%20accountability%20from%20the%20Assam%20police.%20These%20district-level%20authorities%20have%20been%20reduced%20to%20only%20a%20desk%20that%20forwards%20the%20complaints%20received%20further%20up%20than%20initiating%20an%20inquiry%2C%20as%20mandated%20by%20the%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20the%20state%20Police%20Act%20was%20amended%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Assam%20SPAC%20didn%E2%80%99t%20reject%20complaints%20without%20initiating%20an%20inquiry.%20In%202022%20and%202023%20(till%20March)%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20complaints%20were%20closed%20without%20inquiry%2C%20most%20likely%20due%20to%20SPAC%E2%80%99s%20reduced%20mandate%20following%20the%20legislative%20amendments%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%20has%20further%20underlined%20that%20the%20Commission%20no%20longer%20has%20the%20power%20to%20monitor%20the%20pendency%20of%20the%20inquiries%20at%20regular%20intervals.%20Parsing%20the%20data%20provided%20by%20the%20Commission%20through%20RTI%2C%20the%20CHRI%20study%20could%20establish%20that%20there%20has%20been%20a%20%E2%80%9Clow%20number%20of%20recommendations%20for%20departmental%20inquiries%20and%20no%20recommendations%20for%20registration%20of%20FIRs%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20act%20of%20reducing%20the%20SPAC%E2%80%99s%20mandate%20without%20a%20complementary%20increase%20in%20that%20of%20the%20(district%20accountability%20authorities%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20cause%20of%20concern%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20underlined.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20comes%20across%20as%20significant%20in%20the%20study%20is%20that%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20in%20its%20annual%20reports%20have%20been%20ignored%20by%20the%20state%20government.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20its%202018-2022%20annual%20report%2C%20SPAC%20recommended%20that%20the%20state%20government%20allot%20land%20to%20it%20for%20a%20permanent%20office%20building%20so%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20huge%20sum%20of%20money%E2%80%9D%20being%20spent%20towards%20renting%20office%20space%20could%20be%20saved%20by%20the%20state%20exchequer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20noteworthy%20suggestion%20was%20demanding%20accountability%20from%20the%20state%20director%20general%20of%20police%2C%20binding%20an%20obligation%20on%20him%20to%20ensure%20quarterly%20status%20reports%20to%20SPAC%20on%20departmental%20enquiries%20against%20police%20officers.%20Also%20that%20the%20investigation%20of%20an%20FIR%20against%20a%20police%20officer%20should%20be%20conducted%20by%20an%20officer%20senior%20by%20at%20least%20one%20rank%20to%20him%2Fher%20or%20by%20the%20state%20CID.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20no%20action%20stated%20for%20the%20DGP%20if%20he%20falters%20in%20conducting%20inquiries%2C%20the%20accountability%20of%20that%20public%20office%20has%20been%20reduced%20substantially.%20The%20CHRI%20report%20recommends%20that%20to%20make%20SPAC%20act%20as%20per%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20mandate%2C%20%E2%80%9Cunreasonable%20delay%20or%20failure%E2%80%9D%20on%20his%20part%20to%20report%20to%20Assam%20SPAC%20about%20action%20taken%20on%20its%20recommendations%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%9Cmisconduct%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Model%20Police%20Bill%2C%202015%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%2C%20the%20Commission%20is%20headed%20by%20retired%20Gauhati%20high%20court%20Justice%20B.P.%20Katakey%20as%20its%20chairperson%20with%20former%20state%20DGP%20Mukesh%20Sahay%2C%20retired%20IAS%20officer%20Gaurav%20Bohra%20and%20retired%20state%20service%20officer%20Moniratna%20Mahanta%20as%20members.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20has%20highlighted%20that%20their%20tenure%20would%20be%20over%20by%20this%20December%2C%20and%20the%20state%20government%20must%20ensure%20that%20those%20posts%20are%20filled%20in%20time.%20Currently%2C%20though%20the%20SC%20directive%20has%20sought%20one%20of%20its%20members%20to%20be%20a%20woman%20and%20one%20a%20member%20of%20the%20civil%20society%2C%20the%20Assam%20SPAC%20has%20not%20adhered%20to%20it.%20It%20has%20also%20underlined%20that%20the%20Commission%20is%20constituted%20without%20any%20transparency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20Sarma%20government%20came%20to%20power%2C%20Assam%20has%20been%20in%20the%20news%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fthe-nation%2Fassam-under-the-scanner-after-rise-in-cases-of-encounter-deaths-since-2017%2Farticle66790106.ece%5C%22%3Esharp%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%E2%80%98encounter%20deaths%E2%80%99%20by%20state%20police%2C%20leading%20some%20civil%20society%20groups%20to%20seek%20the%20Gauhati%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20to%20inquire%20into%20it.%20Chief%20minist