re%20also%20going%20to%20highlight%20the%20helplessness%20of%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20who%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20puppet%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20bureaucrat-turned-politician%20V.K.%20Pandian.%20We%20will%20also%20tell%20people%20that%20the%20BJD%20and%20BJP%20are%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20same%20coin%2C%E2%80%9D%20continued%20Jena%2C%20who%20thinks%20that%20the%20Congress%20which%20has%20been%20going%20through%20a%20bad%20phase%20in%20Odisha%20stands%20a%20good%20chance%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20media%20persons%20after%20the%20meeting%20with%20AICC%20bigwigs%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Sarat%20Pattnayak%20said%20that%20the%20party%20would%20step%20up%20its%20fight%20against%20the%20BJD%20and%20BJP%2C%20which%20he%20said%20are%20equally%20corrupt.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20discussed%20the%20strategy%20for%202024.%20The%20biggest%20issue%20against%20the%20state%20government%20is%20corruption%20and%20the%20number%20of%20scams%20that%20are%20taking%20place%2C%E2%80%9D%20averred%20Pattnayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20senior%20party%20leaders%2C%20including%20general%20secretary%20and%20former%20MLA%20Lalatendu%20Mohapatra%2C%20also%20exuded%20confidence%20about%20the%20party%20doing%20better%20in%20the%20coming%20elections%20compared%20to%20the%20past.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20better%20prepared%20this%20time%20and%20the%20strategic%20meeting%20held%20in%20Delhi%20is%20going%20to%20help%20us%20a%20lot.%20The%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20that%20people%20of%20the%20state%20now%20know%20that%20BJP%20and%20BJD%20are%20having%20a%20fixed%20bout%20in%20Odisha.%20They%20are%20going%20to%20reject%20both%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mohapatra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20optimism%20of%20state%20Congress%20leaders%2C%20things%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20easy%20for%20the%20party%20if%20its%20record%20in%20the%20state%20is%20anything%20to%20go%20by.%20Plagued%20by%20factional%20feuds%2C%20the%20fortunes%20of%20the%20party%20have%20been%20declining%20consistently%20in%20Odisha%20since%202000%2C%20when%20it%20was%20thrown%20out%20of%20power%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20disastrous%20super-cyclone%20that%20generated%20a%20wave%20of%20public%20anger.%20A%20BJD-BJP%20coalition%20government%20led%20by%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20came%20to%20power%20in%202000%20and%20even%20though%20the%20coalition%20collapsed%20in%202009%2C%20with%20the%20BJP%20pulling%20out%2C%20Patnaik%20remains%20in%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB-300x153.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB-1024x523.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678686%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22613%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOdisha%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40Naveen_Odisha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20BJD%20won%20103%20assembly%20and%2014%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20the%20simultaneously%20held%20polls%20in%202009%2C%20the%20Congress%20could%20manage%2027%20assembly%20and%20six%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20those%20elections.%20The%20BJP%20was%20reduced%20to%20a%20single-digit%20(6)%20figure%20in%20the%20147-strong%20state%20assembly.%20It%20failed%20to%20win%20even%20a%20single%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%202014%20elections%2C%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20in%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20nosedived%20to%2026%25%20from%2032.75%25%20in%202009.%20The%20party%20won%2016%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20but%20could%20not%20open%20its%20account%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20In%20sharp%20contrast%2C%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik-led%20BJD%20swept%20the%20polls%20%E2%80%93%20grabbing%2020%20of%20the%2021%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20and%20117%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20The%20BJP%20won%2010%20assembly%20seats%20and%20the%20Sundergarh%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20hit%20rock%20bottom%20in%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20when%20it%20won%20just%20nine%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%2C%20losing%20the%20tag%20of%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%20to%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%93%20which%20bagged%2023%20seats.%20In%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%20a%20consolation%20victory%20in%20Koraput%2C%20where%20its%20candidate%20scraped%20through%20by%20a%20narrow%20margin.%20The%20main%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20plummeting%20fortunes%20in%20Odisha%20has%20been%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20not%20only%20emerged%20as%20the%20main%20opposition%20party.%20Its%20Lok%20Sabha%20tally%20went%20from%201%20to%208%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20initial%20days%20of%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20slide%20in%20the%20state%2C%20the%20party%20which%20gained%20most%20was%20the%20BJD.%20But%20as%20its%20decline%20became%20more%20acute%2C%20it%20was%20the%20BJP%20which%20started%20benefitting.%20Erstwhile%20Congress%20loyalists%20transferred%20their%20votes%20to%20the%20party.%20In%20the%20latest%20phase%20which%20began%20in%202019%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20near%20decimation%20in%20the%20state.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20any%20chance%20of%20its%20revival.%20The%20BJP%20will%20gain%20from%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20fall%20and%20the%20anti-incumbency%20factor%20which%20is%20going%20to%20hit%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20state%20BJP%20general%20secretary%20Bhrigu%20Buxipatra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20panchayat%20elections%20held%20in%20the%20state%20in%202017%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20made%20major%20gains%20with%20its%20zila%20parishad%20tally%20going%20up%20to%20297%20from%2036%20in%202012%2C%20mainly%20because%20of%20a%20sharp%20decline%20in%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20%E2%80%93%20its%20total%20zila%20parishad%20seats%20came%20down%20to%2060%20from%20126.%20However%2C%20in%20the%202022%20rural%20polls%2C%20when%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20ZP%20tally%20went%20down%20further%20to%2037%2C%20it%20was%20the%20BJD%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodishas-panchayat-poll-outcome-seals-naveen-patnaiks-invincibility%5C%22%3Egained%20the%20most%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20claiming%20a%20record%20number%20of%20766%20zila%20parishad%20seats.%20The%20BJP%20also%20suffered%20a%20massive%20jolt%2C%20getting%20reduced%20to%2042%20ZP%20seats%20from%20297.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sharp%20decline%20in%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20fortunes%20in%20Odisha%20can%20be%20directly%20attributed%20to%20the%20internal%20feuds%2C%20which%20have%20prevented%20it%20from%20presenting%20a%20united%20face%20in%20the%20elections.%20Most%20of%20the%20PCC%20presidents%20have%20had%20to%20struggle%20with%20this%20problem%20and%20Sarat%20Pattnayak%2C%20who%20took%20over%20from%20Niranjan%20Patnaik%20in%20May%20last%20year%2C%20is%20no%20exception.%20His%20running%20feud%20with%20senior%20party%20leaders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbhubaneswar%2Fcongress-suspends-moquim-and-biswal%2Farticleshow%2F101793485.cms%23%5C%22%3EChiranjib%20Biswal%20and%20Mohammed%20Moquim%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20MLA%20from%20Barabati-Cuttack%2C%20has%20been%20the%20talk%20of%20party%20circles.%20Both%20the%20leaders%20were%20suspended%20by%20him%20a%20few%20months%20ago%20on%20the%20charges%20of%20indulging%20in%20anti-party%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20Niranjan%20Patnaik%E2%80%99s%20term%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20he%20faced%20a%20virtual%20revolt%20when%20then%20state%20party%20working%20president%2C%20Naba%20Kishore%20Das%2C%20who%20was%20an%20MLA%20from%20Jharsuguda%2C%20quit%20the%20party%20along%20with%20his%20colleague%20from%20Sundergarh%20Jogesh%20Singh.%20Das%20won%20the%20election%20on%20a%20BJD%20ticket%20and%20became%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20government.%20He%20was%20assassinated%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fodisha-minister-naba-kisore-das-dies-hours-after-being-shot-at-by-cop%5C%22%3EJanuary%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20exit%20from%20the%20party%20was%20an%20embarrassment%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%20which%20faced%20another%20rebellion%20when%20former%20Union%20minister%20Srikant%20Jena%20and%20his%20prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9%2C%20former%20Koraput%20MLA%20Krushna%20Chandra%20Sagaria%2C%20raised%20some%20prickly%20issues%20plaguing%20the%20state%20Congress%20and%20were%20expelled%20from%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20analyst%20Shashi%20Kant%20Mishra%20believes%20that%20the%20problem%20of%20infighting%20and%20bickering%20in%20the%20state%20Congress%20is%20unlikely%20to%20end%20anytime%20soon.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20the%20bane%20of%20the%20party.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20any%20realistic%20chance%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20revival%20in%20the%20state%20unless%20this%20problem%20is%20addressed%20effectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mishra.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703235264000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F18143119%2FSIRSA-GENERAL-PICS.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodish-congress-hope-revival-bjd-bjp%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Things%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20easy%20for%20the%20party%20if%20its%20record%20in%20the%20state%20is%20anything%20to%20go%20by.%20Its%20vote%20share%20and%20seat%20tallies%20have%20consistently%20declined%20since%202009.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodish-congress-hope-revival-bjd-bjp%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20Remained%20India's%20Biggest%20Source%20of%20Crude%20Oil%20Imports%20in%20October%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F23133402%2FBharat_Petroleum_Petrol_Pump_near_Nagpur.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ERussia%20accounted%20for%20nearly%2030%25%20of%20the%20crude%20oil%20imported%20to%20India%20in%20October%2C%20and%20remained%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20source%20for%20oil%20imports%2C%20according%20to%20official%20data.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Frussia-oil-imports-rise-44-in-october-11703183160455.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELivemint%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20value%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20supply%20to%20India%20in%20the%20month%20stood%20at%20%243.78%20billion%2C%20which%20was%20a%2044%25%20year-on-year%20increase%20from%20October%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20increase%20in%20October%20imports%20was%20triggered%20by%20increased%20demand%20for%20petroleum%20products%20in%20the%20festive%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COverall%2C%20in%20the%20April-October%20period%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20crude%20import%20bill%20actually%20fell%2019.53%25%20y-o-y%20to%20%2476.57%20billion.%20But%20imports%20from%20Russia%20have%20increased%2083.95%25%20in%20the%20same%20period%20to%20%2426.9%20billion%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ELivemint%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20began%2C%20Russia%20accounted%20for%20only%202%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20oil%20imports%2C%20behind%20Iraq%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE.%20But%20after%20the%20war%20and%20US-led%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%2C%20Russia%20offered%20b